A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
AN ACT
1 To amend Chapter 8 of Title 35 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated, relating to
2 employment and training of peace officers, so as to prohibit individuals who have been
3 members of hate groups from serving in law enforcement and the organized militia under
4 certain circumstances; to provide for definitions; to provide for enforcement and screening;
5 to provide for appeals; to provide for public reporting; to provide for related matters; to
6 provide for a short title; to provide for legislative findings; to repeal conflicting laws; and for
7 other purposes.
8 BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF GEORGIA:
9 SECTION 1.
10 This Act shall be known and may be cited as the "Hate-Free Heroes Act."
11 SECTION 2.
12 The General Assembly finds that:
13 (1) Public safety officials play a critical role in maintaining trust, security, and fairness in
14 diverse communities;
