41 (d)(1) An individual may appeal a finding of hate group affiliation by providing evidence
42 to the council demonstrating:
43 (A) His or her departure from the group and disavowal of its principles; and
44 (B) Actions taken to counteract or rectify harm caused by his or her past affiliation.
45 (2) The council shall have the discretion to approve appeals on a case-by-case basis.
46 (e) Annual reports detailing the enforcement of this Code section shall be published by the
47 council, including:
48 (1) The number of individuals denied peace officer roles and state militia roles based on
49 hate group affiliation;
50 (2) Appeals filed and outcomes of such cases; and
51 (3) Updates to the list of identified hate groups."
52 SECTION 4.
53 All laws and parts of laws in conflict with this Act are repealed.
